  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite its lack of citations and online mentions, \"Brokers of Modernity,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2019, has begun to carve out a niche in scholarly discourse, as evidenced by its commercial linkage and relevance to policy sustainability.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Brokers of Modernity\" offers a significant contribution to the academic landscape, particularly those exploring the intersections of societal change and institutional roles. Although the publication currently has no recorded citations or mentions on platforms like Wikipedia or Reddit, it is available for purchase on commercial sites such as Amazon and Goodreads, suggesting that there is a market interest in its themes.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The work reflects a strong connection to contemporary issues, indicated by its association with at least one Sustainable Development Goal (SDG). This underscores its potential relevance to policy discussions and societal applications. The book’s engagement with themes of modernity and brokerage provides a valuable perspective for researchers and practitioners interested in understanding the complexities of modern social structures.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While no quantifiable usage metrics from data repositories are available, the book's positive signals of commercial linkage indicate that it might impact readers beyond academic circles. The absence of community discourse online, represented by the lack of discussions on platforms like Reddit or Bluesky, does raise questions about its broader societal reach. However, the initial indicators of visibility in commercial spaces could point to future academic uptake as awareness builds.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Ultimately, \"Brokers of Modernity\" embodies a scholarly work poised to influence both academic and policy domains, even though it has not yet achieved significant visibility or engagement metrics. As this publication gains traction, it will be valuable to monitor its growth in citations and community discourse, which could solidify its role in contemporary academic discussions.</p>",
